This paper deals with cross-lingual transfer of dependency parsers, which is a topic that falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also makes use of machine learning techniques, such as clustering and annotation projection, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves techniques for lexical transfer and integration of different methods, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of the Bible as a source of translation data, which could suggest a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) or distributed computing (cs.DC).
